<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Ding Wu</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --text: #222;
      --muted: #666;
      --line: #e5e7eb;
      --link: #2563eb;
      --bg: #ffffff;
      --soft: #f8fafc;
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      color: var(--text);
      background: var(--bg);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--link);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    .page {
      max-width: 1080px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 36px 24px 60px;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 260px 1fr;
      gap: 48px;
    }

    .sidebar {
      position: sticky;
      top: 28px;
      align-self: start;
      border-right: 1px solid var(--line);
      padding-right: 28px;
    }

    .avatar {
      width: 160px;
      height: 160px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      object-fit: cover;
      background: var(--soft);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .name {
      font-size: 28px;
      line-height: 1.2;
      margin: 0 0 6px;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .title {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 15px;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .contact {
      font-size: 15px;
      margin: 18px 0;
    }

    .contact div {
      margin: 6px 0;
    }

    .nav {
      margin-top: 24px;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 8px;
      font-size: 15px;
    }

    .nav a {
      color: #333;
    }

    main {
      min-width: 0;
    }

    section {
      margin-bottom: 36px;
      padding-bottom: 24px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }

    section:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin: 0 0 16px;
      line-height: 1.25;
    }

    h3 {
      font-size: 18px;
      margin: 22px 0 8px;
    }

    p {
      margin: 0 0 14px;
    }

    ul {
      margin: 0;
      padding-left: 22px;
    }

    li {
      margin: 8px 0;
    }

    .item {
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .item-title {
      font-weight: 650;
    }

    .meta {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 14px;
      margin-top: 2px;
    }

    .tagline {
      background: var(--soft);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 16px 18px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
      color: #333;
    }

    .project-links {
      margin-top: 6px;
      font-size: 14px;
    }

    footer {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 13px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

    @media (max-width: 760px) {
      .page {
        display: block;
        padding: 26px 18px 42px;
      }

      .sidebar {
        position: static;
        border-right: none;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding-right: 0;
        padding-bottom: 24px;
        margin-bottom: 30px;
      }

      .avatar {
        width: 132px;
        height: 132px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="page">
    <aside class="sidebar">
      <!-- Replace avatar.jpg with your own photo file, or delete this line if you do not want a photo. -->
      <img class="avatar" src="avatar.jpg" alt="Ding Wu" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
      <h1 class="name">Ding Wu</h1>
      <div class="title">AI Researcher · LLMs · RAG · Information Retrieval</div>

      <div class="contact">
        <div><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:wuding97@gmail.com">wuding97@gmail.com</a></div>
        <div><strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/dingwucs">dingwucs</a></div>
        <div><strong>Location:</strong> Suzhou / Shanghai / Remote</div>
      </div>

      <nav class="nav">
        <a href="#about">About</a>
        <a href="#education">Education</a>
        <a href="#interests">Research Interests</a>
        <a href="#projects">Selected Projects</a>
        <a href="#news">News</a>
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <main>
      <section id="about">
        <div class="tagline">
          I am interested in building reliable, efficient, and knowledge-aware AI systems, with a current focus on retrieval-augmented generation, LLM evaluation, information retrieval, and graph-based reasoning.
        </div>
        <h2>About</h2>
        <p>
          I am a researcher working at the intersection of artificial intelligence, digital finance, and industrial innovation. My current research interests center on large language models, retrieval-augmented generation, information retrieval, and knowledge-augmented AI systems.
        </p>
        <p>
          Before moving toward computer science research, I received interdisciplinary training in economics, statistics, and data analytics. I am currently preparing research projects and manuscripts in RAG, LLM evaluation, and retrieval systems, with the long-term goal of pursuing a Ph.D. in Computer Science.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="education">
        <h2>Education</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Georgia Institute of Technology</strong>, M.S. in Computer Science, OMSCS, expected Fall 2026</li>
          <li><strong>University of Pennsylvania</strong>, M.S. in Social Policy and Data Analytics</li>
          <li><strong>Fudan University</strong>, B.A. / B.S. in Mathematical Economics</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="interests">
        <h2>Research Interests</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Retrieval-Augmented Generation and knowledge-augmented language models</li>
          <li>Information retrieval, multi-hop retrieval, and graph-based retrieval</li>
          <li>LLM evaluation, reasoning reliability, and hallucination detection</li>
          <li>Efficient adaptation and training-free methods for large language models</li>
          <li>Applied machine learning for finance, manufacturing, and industrial services</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="projects">
        <h2>Selected Research Projects</h2>

        <div class="item">
          <div class="item-title">Query-Aware Flow Diffusion for Graph-Based RAG</div>
          <div class="meta">Manuscript in preparation · Retrieval-Augmented Generation · Graph Retrieval</div>
          <p>
            A training-free framework for query-aware edge reweighting and adaptive graph traversal in graph-based RAG. The project explores how flow diffusion can improve subgraph recovery and reduce unnecessary LLM calls in multi-hop question answering.
          </p>
          <div class="project-links">[Paper coming soon] [Code coming soon]</div>
        </div>

        <div class="item">
          <div class="item-title">Compression and Uncertainty Signals for Passage-Level RAG</div>
          <div class="meta">Research project · RAG Efficiency · Uncertainty Estimation</div>
          <p>
            This project studies whether bottleneck-style compression and uncertainty signals can help distinguish useful passages from distractors while maintaining answer quality in retrieval-augmented generation.
          </p>
          <div class="project-links">[Code coming soon]</div>
        </div>

        <div class="item">
          <div class="item-title">LLM Evaluation for Knowledge-Intensive Tasks</div>
          <div class="meta">Ongoing · LLM Evaluation · Information Retrieval</div>
          <p>
            A practical evaluation track for testing LLM reliability on knowledge-intensive and retrieval-dependent tasks, with emphasis on reproducible experiments, clear baselines, and error analysis.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="news">
        <h2>News and Updates</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>May 2026:</strong> Building research projects in RAG, LLM evaluation, and information retrieval.</li>
          <li><strong>2026:</strong> Preparing for Georgia Tech OMSCS and future Ph.D. applications in Computer Science.</li>
          <li><strong>2025–2026:</strong> Exploring AI applications in digital finance and industrial innovation.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <footer>
        © 2026 Ding Wu. Built with GitHub Pages.
      </footer>
    </main>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
